# Atlas CertOps
## Disaster Recovery Guide

Version 1.0

Document Owner: Atlas & Else
Classification: Internal / Customer Administrator
Review Cycle: Annual

---

# 1. Purpose

This document defines the procedures for restoring Atlas CertOps after a service interruption, infrastructure failure, or catastrophic event.

The objective is to restore operations quickly while maintaining the integrity, confidentiality, and availability of customer data.

---

# 2. Recovery Objectives

Recovery Time Objective (RTO)

Target:
4 Hours

Recovery Point Objective (RPO)

Target:
15 Minutes

Actual recovery objectives may vary based on customer deployment and subscription tier.

---

# 3. Disaster Scenarios

Examples include:

• Cloud region outage
• Database corruption
• Storage failure
• Ransomware
• Accidental deletion
• Infrastructure misconfiguration
• DNS failure
• TLS certificate expiration
• Third-party authentication outage
• Complete platform outage

